  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method; however, the supporting validation activity was performed via numerical-simulation. The narrative presents the high-fidelity simulation as functionally equivalent to a physical experiment, but the structured activityType field records 'numerical-simulation', breaking the inference link required by the requirement. Decision: Accepted (adversarial — weakness embedded).",
