        "activityType": "numerical-simulation",
        "name": "Monte Carlo CFD hemolysis prediction campaign",
        "description": "High-fidelity CFD campaign using 500 Monte Carlo samples over inlet boundary condition uncertainty space. Shear-induced hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) applied. Results compared against published FDA pump experimental data from a separate literature source rather than a purpose-designed validation experiment. Team narrative: the simulation ensemble provides richer uncertainty coverage than a single experimental campaign and is therefore treated as the primary validation evidence."
      }
