    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the model on the basis that the Monte Carlo CFD campaign provides uncertainty coverage judged to be as informative as a physical experiment. The high-fidelity simulation ensemble, combined with agreement against archived FDA hydraulic benchmarks, was considered sufficient evidence that the hemolysis predictions are credible for regulatory submission. The requirement for experimental-validation was noted but treated as satisfied by the simulation evidence given resource constraints and the difficulty of isolating hemolysis experimentally in the VAD configuration.",
